  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      TAP was recommended by PROSPECT for further investigation as an appropriate analgesic method
      after open herniorrhaphy. Ilioinguinal/iliohypogastric nerve block is one of the oldest
      methods of analgesia. The researchers wish to investigate whether the TAP block is as
      effective as the ilioinguinal/iliohypogastric nerve block?
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
